section.section:
This subsection does not apply to:
An assignment of a mortgage or if presented for recordation, an assignment of a deed of trust;
A release of a deed of trust or mortgage;
A substitution of trustees on a deed of trust;
A power of attorney; or
A financing statement or an amendment, continuation, release, or termination of a financing statement recorded in land records.

A complete intake sheet shall:
Describe the property by at least one of the following property identifiers:
The property tax account identification number, if any, or in Montgomery County, any parcel identifier required under § 3-501 of this title, if different from the tax account number;
The street address, if any;
If the property is a lot within a subdivided tract, the lot and block designation, or in Baltimore City, the current land record block number;
If the property is part of a tract that has been subdivided informally and there is neither an assigned tax account identification number for the parcel nor a lot and block designation, then the street address, if any, or the amount of acreage; or
If the property consists of multiple parcels, the designation "various lots of ground" or the abbreviation "VAR. L.O.G.";
Name each grantor, donor, mortgagor, and assignor and each grantee, donee, mortgagee, and assignee;
State the type of instrument;
State the amount of consideration payable, including the amount of any mortgage or deed of trust indebtedness assumed, or the principal amount of debt secured;
State the amount of recording charges due, including the land records surcharge and any transfer and recordation taxes;
Identify, by citation or explanation, each claimed exemption from recording taxes;
For an instrument effecting a change in ownership, state a tax bill mailing address; and
Indicate the person to whom the instrument is to be returned.
